<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
  <title>Brave UX - Work - CDS</title>
  <%- include ../partials/_head %>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="wrapper case-study cds">
    <header class="case-header overlay">
      <div class="case-header-content right container">
        <h5 class="case-header-client-name">Congressional Digital Service</h5>
        <h1 class="case-header-tagline">Pull talented tech and&nbsp;<br />Hill staff together to&nbsp;<br />rebuild Congress</h1>
        <h6 class="case-header-type">Brand and Website Content, Design, and Build</h6>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="case-exec-summary padded blue">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="case-exec-summary-text">We designed and built the brand strategy for an incredible&#32;<br />organization that is fixing Congress’s tech problems.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-breakdown padded tan">
      <div class="container row between">
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Challenge</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            Inspire leaders to lead
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            We set out to create and execute a brand that motivated the right people in Congress and tech to get involved.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Solution</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            Give patriotism a refresh
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            We built the brand around people with the drive to cut through red tape and truly make a difference.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Scope</p>
          <ul class="case-breakdown-list">
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Visual Branding</li>
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Website Design</li>
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Content Strategy &amp; Writing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded-top overflow">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-right padded-bottom">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">Cut to the heart of your audience</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              Members of Congress and technologists seem very different. But what drives the best of both worlds? Duty. Honor. And cutting through the muck.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl cds-devices">
          <div class="frame frame-desktop edge-bottom shadow sr-right lazy-ratio" data-width="3054" data-height="2234">
            <img src="./images/work/cds/homepage.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          </div>
          <div class="frame frame-mobile absolute sr-fade sr-delay-double">
            <div class="frame-container">
              <img src="./images/work/cds/homepage-mobile.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <img src="./images/work/cds/congress.jpg" alt="" class="block-image">
    </section>

    <section class="block row">
      <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md padded column half-md blue">
        <div class="inner-block-content container">
          <h2 class="case-block-heading">America, the beautiful</h2>
          <p class="case-block-text">
            We took recognizable symbols – the flag, seats of Congress – and turned their shapes, colors, and patterns into a unique brand system.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block column half-md hide-overflow dark-blue">
        <div class="lazy-ratio" data-width="136" data-height="150">
          <img src="./images/work/cds/cds-congress.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image sr-right">
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded-top gray">
      <div class="inner-block padded-bottom row absolute-center-md">
        <div class="inner-block-content content-centered container">
          <h2 class="case-block-heading">A website for sore eyes</h2>
          <p class="case-block-text">
            We created a gorgeous, easy-to-navigate site where the Congressional Digital Service mission, message, and visuals tell the same story.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block row">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <div class="frame frame-desktop edge-bottom shadow sr-tall lazy-ratio" data-width="1441" data-height="1514">
            <img src="./images/work/cds/homepage-cards.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block blue">
      <div class="lazy-ratio" data-width="163" data-height="150">
        <img src="./images/work/cds/how-it-works.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image">
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block row">
      <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md padded column half-md tan">
        <div class="inner-block-content container">
          <h2 class="case-block-heading">We see branding with our eyes closed</h2>
          <p class="case-block-text">
            Our brand system passes an important test: it’s simple enough to remember with your eyes closed. Leaving a strong impression often means being bold enough to keep it simple.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block column half-md hide-overflow">
        <div class="inner-box dark-red">
          <img src="./images/work/cds/branding-top.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image full-height  sr-right">
        </div>
        <div class="inner-box red">
          <img src="./images/work/cds/branding-bottom.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image full-height  sr-left">
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded dark-blue">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="lazy-ratio" data-width="300" data-height="116">
            <img src="./images/work/cds/logo.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain sr-reveal">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md gutter-bottom-mobile order-top-xs column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-left">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">A logo with deeper (and double) meaning</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              Our tech audience may see their file URI (://) in our clever remix of the American flag.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-referral row">
      <div class="inner-block padded column absolute-center-xs half-md blue">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="case-referral-blockquote">Brave UX feels like a true member of our team</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block padded column half-md gray">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="case-referral-quote-icon"></div>
          <p class="case-referral-text">The most important thing about Brave UX is partnership and empathy. Every other designer or design team I've worked with has felt like a business deal. Brave UX feels like a true member of our team, walking not just a mile in our shoes but a hundred in order to deliver the most spot-on us brand and designs I’ve ever seen. That is who they are and what they are all about, and what sets them leagues apart from the crowd.</p>
          <p class="case-referral-author">Seamus Kraft, <em>Founder, Congressional Digital Service</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <%- include ../partials/_footer-scripts %>

</body>
</html>
